40static void
41nv04_devinit_meminit(struct nvkm_devinit *init)
42{
43 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &init->subdev;
44 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
45 u32 patt = 0xdeadbeef;
46 struct io_mapping *fb;
47 int i;
48
49 /* Map the framebuffer aperture */
50 fb = fbmem_init(device);
51 if (!fb) {
52 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to map fb\n");
53 return;
54 }
55
56 /* Sequencer and refresh off */
57 nvkm_wrvgas(device, 0, 1, nvkm_rdvgas(device, 0, 1) | 0x20);
58 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_DEBUG_0, 0, NV04_PFB_DEBUG_0_REFRESH_OFF);
59
60 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0, ~0,
61 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT_16MB |
62 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_WIDTH_128 |
63 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_TYPE_SGRAM_16MBIT);
64
65 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
66 fbmem_poke(fb, 4 * i, patt);
67
68 fbmem_poke(fb, 0x400000, patt + 1);
69
70 if (fbmem_peek(fb, 0) == patt + 1) {
71 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0,
72 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_TYPE,
73 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_TYPE_SDRAM_16MBIT);
74 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_DEBUG_0,
75 NV04_PFB_DEBUG_0_REFRESH_OFF, 0);
76
77 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
78 fbmem_poke(fb, 4 * i, patt);
79
80 if ((fbmem_peek(fb, 0xc) & 0xffff) != (patt & 0xffff))
81 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0,
82 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_WIDTH_128 |
83 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT,
84 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT_8MB);
85 } else
86 if ((fbmem_peek(fb, 0xc) & 0xffff0000) != (patt & 0xffff0000)) {
87 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0,
88 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_WIDTH_128 |
89 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT,
90 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT_4MB);
91 } else
92 if (fbmem_peek(fb, 0) != patt) {
93 if (fbmem_readback(fb, 0x800000, patt))
94 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0,
95 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT,
96 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT_8MB);
97 else
98 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0,
99 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT,
100 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT_4MB);
101
102 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_TYPE,
103 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_TYPE_SGRAM_8MBIT);
104 } else
105 if (!fbmem_readback(fb, 0x800000, patt)) {
106 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0, NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT,
107 NV04_PFB_BOOT_0_RAM_AMOUNT_8MB);
108
109 }
110
111 /* Refresh on, sequencer on */
112 nvkm_mask(device, NV04_PFB_DEBUG_0, NV04_PFB_DEBUG_0_REFRESH_OFF, 0);
113 nvkm_wrvgas(device, 0, 1, nvkm_rdvgas(device, 0, 1) & ~0x20);
114 fbmem_fini(fb);
115}

117static int
118powerctrl_1_shift(int chip_version, int reg)
119{
120 int shift = -4;
121
122 if (chip_version < 0x17 || chip_version == 0x1a || chip_version == 0x20)
123 return shift;
124
125 switch (reg) {
126 case 0x680520:
127 shift += 4;
128 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
129 case 0x680508:
130 shift += 4;
131 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
132 case 0x680504:
133 shift += 4;
134 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
135 case 0x680500:
136 shift += 4;
137 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
138 }
139
140 /*
141 * the shift for vpll regs is only used for nv3x chips with a single
142 * stage pll
143 */
144 if (shift > 4 && (chip_version < 0x32 || chip_version == 0x35 ||
145 chip_version == 0x36 || chip_version >= 0x40))
146 shift = -4;
147
148 return shift;
149}
150
151void
152setPLL_single(struct nvkm_devinit *init, u32 reg,
153 struct nvkm_pll_vals *pv)
154{
155 struct nvkm_device *device = init->subdev.device;
156 int chip_version = device->bios->version.chip;
157 uint32_t oldpll = nvkm_rd32(device, reg);
158 int oldN = (oldpll >> 8) & 0xff, oldM = oldpll & 0xff;
159 uint32_t pll = (oldpll & 0xfff80000) | pv->log2P << 16 | pv->NM1;
160 uint32_t saved_powerctrl_1 = 0;
161 int shift_powerctrl_1 = powerctrl_1_shift(chip_version, reg);
162
163 if (oldpll == pll)
164 return; /* already set */
165
166 if (shift_powerctrl_1 >= 0) {
167 saved_powerctrl_1 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x001584);
168 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001584,
169 (saved_powerctrl_1 & ~(0xf << shift_powerctrl_1)) |
170 1 << shift_powerctrl_1);
171 }
172
173 if (oldM && pv->M1 && (oldN / oldM < pv->N1 / pv->M1))
174 /* upclock -- write new post divider first */
175 nvkm_wr32(device, reg, pv->log2P << 16 | (oldpll & 0xffff));
176 else
177 /* downclock -- write new NM first */
178 nvkm_wr32(device, reg, (oldpll & 0xffff0000) | pv->NM1);
179
180 if ((chip_version < 0x17 || chip_version == 0x1a) &&
181 chip_version != 0x11)
182 /* wait a bit on older chips */
183 msleep(64);
184 nvkm_rd32(device, reg);
185
186 /* then write the other half as well */
187 nvkm_wr32(device, reg, pll);
188
189 if (shift_powerctrl_1 >= 0)
190 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001584, saved_powerctrl_1);
191}
192
193static uint32_t
194new_ramdac580(uint32_t reg1, bool ss, uint32_t ramdac580)
195{
196 bool head_a = (reg1 == 0x680508);
197
198 if (ss) /* single stage pll mode */
199 ramdac580 |= head_a ? 0x00000100 : 0x10000000;
200 else
201 ramdac580 &= head_a ? 0xfffffeff : 0xefffffff;
202
203 return ramdac580;
204}
205
206void
207setPLL_double_highregs(struct nvkm_devinit *init, u32 reg1,
208 struct nvkm_pll_vals *pv)
209{
210 struct nvkm_device *device = init->subdev.device;
211 int chip_version = device->bios->version.chip;
212 bool nv3035 = chip_version == 0x30 || chip_version == 0x35;
213 uint32_t reg2 = reg1 + ((reg1 == 0x680520) ? 0x5c : 0x70);
214 uint32_t oldpll1 = nvkm_rd32(device, reg1);
215 uint32_t oldpll2 = !nv3035 ? nvkm_rd32(device, reg2) : 0;
216 uint32_t pll1 = (oldpll1 & 0xfff80000) | pv->log2P << 16 | pv->NM1;
217 uint32_t pll2 = (oldpll2 & 0x7fff0000) | 1 << 31 | pv->NM2;
218 uint32_t oldramdac580 = 0, ramdac580 = 0;
219 bool single_stage = !pv->NM2 || pv->N2 == pv->M2; /* nv41+ only */
220 uint32_t saved_powerctrl_1 = 0, savedc040 = 0;
221 int shift_powerctrl_1 = powerctrl_1_shift(chip_version, reg1);
222
223 /* model specific additions to generic pll1 and pll2 set up above */
224 if (nv3035) {
225 pll1 = (pll1 & 0xfcc7ffff) | (pv->N2 & 0x18) << 21 |
226 (pv->N2 & 0x7) << 19 | 8 << 4 | (pv->M2 & 7) << 4;
227 pll2 = 0;
228 }
229 if (chip_version > 0x40 && reg1 >= 0x680508) { /* !nv40 */
230 oldramdac580 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x680580);
231 ramdac580 = new_ramdac580(reg1, single_stage, oldramdac580);
232 if (oldramdac580 != ramdac580)
233 oldpll1 = ~0; /* force mismatch */
234 if (single_stage)
235 /* magic value used by nvidia in single stage mode */
236 pll2 |= 0x011f;
237 }
238 if (chip_version > 0x70)
239 /* magic bits set by the blob (but not the bios) on g71-73 */
240 pll1 = (pll1 & 0x7fffffff) | (single_stage ? 0x4 : 0xc) << 28;
241
242 if (oldpll1 == pll1 && oldpll2 == pll2)
243 return; /* already set */
244
245 if (shift_powerctrl_1 >= 0) {
246 saved_powerctrl_1 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x001584);
247 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001584,
248 (saved_powerctrl_1 & ~(0xf << shift_powerctrl_1)) |
249 1 << shift_powerctrl_1);
250 }
251
252 if (chip_version >= 0x40) {
253 int shift_c040 = 14;
254
255 switch (reg1) {
256 case 0x680504:
257 shift_c040 += 2;
258 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
259 case 0x680500:
260 shift_c040 += 2;
261 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
262 case 0x680520:
263 shift_c040 += 2;
264 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
265 case 0x680508:
266 shift_c040 += 2;
267 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
268 }
269
270 savedc040 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0xc040);
271 if (shift_c040 != 14)
272 nvkm_wr32(device, 0xc040, savedc040 & ~(3 << shift_c040));
273 }
274
275 if (oldramdac580 != ramdac580)
276 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x680580, ramdac580);
277
278 if (!nv3035)
279 nvkm_wr32(device, reg2, pll2);
280 nvkm_wr32(device, reg1, pll1);
281
282 if (shift_powerctrl_1 >= 0)
283 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001584, saved_powerctrl_1);
284 if (chip_version >= 0x40)
285 nvkm_wr32(device, 0xc040, savedc040);
286}
287
288void
289setPLL_double_lowregs(struct nvkm_devinit *init, u32 NMNMreg,
290 struct nvkm_pll_vals *pv)
291{
292 /* When setting PLLs, there is a merry game of disabling and enabling
293 * various bits of hardware during the process. This function is a
294 * synthesis of six nv4x traces, nearly each card doing a subtly
295 * different thing. With luck all the necessary bits for each card are
296 * combined herein. Without luck it deviates from each card's formula
297 * so as to not work on any :)
298 */
299 struct nvkm_device *device = init->subdev.device;
300 uint32_t Preg = NMNMreg - 4;
301 bool mpll = Preg == 0x4020;
302 uint32_t oldPval = nvkm_rd32(device, Preg);
303 uint32_t NMNM = pv->NM2 << 16 | pv->NM1;
304 uint32_t Pval = (oldPval & (mpll ? ~(0x77 << 16) : ~(7 << 16))) |
305 0xc << 28 | pv->log2P << 16;
306 uint32_t saved4600 = 0;
307 /* some cards have different maskc040s */
308 uint32_t maskc040 = ~(3 << 14), savedc040;
309 bool single_stage = !pv->NM2 || pv->N2 == pv->M2;
310
311 if (nvkm_rd32(device, NMNMreg) == NMNM && (oldPval & 0xc0070000) == Pval)
312 return;
313
314 if (Preg == 0x4000)
315 maskc040 = ~0x333;
316 if (Preg == 0x4058)
317 maskc040 = ~(0xc << 24);
318
319 if (mpll) {
320 struct nvbios_pll info;
321 uint8_t Pval2;
322
323 if (nvbios_pll_parse(device->bios, Preg, &info))
324 return;
325
326 Pval2 = pv->log2P + info.bias_p;
327 if (Pval2 > info.max_p)
328 Pval2 = info.max_p;
329 Pval |= 1 << 28 | Pval2 << 20;
330
331 saved4600 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x4600);
332 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4600, saved4600 | 8 << 28);
333 }
334 if (single_stage)
335 Pval |= mpll ? 1 << 12 : 1 << 8;
336
337 nvkm_wr32(device, Preg, oldPval | 1 << 28);
338 nvkm_wr32(device, Preg, Pval & ~(4 << 28));
339 if (mpll) {
340 Pval |= 8 << 20;
341 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4020, Pval & ~(0xc << 28));
342 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4038, Pval & ~(0xc << 28));
343 }
344
345 savedc040 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0xc040);
346 nvkm_wr32(device, 0xc040, savedc040 & maskc040);
347
348 nvkm_wr32(device, NMNMreg, NMNM);
349 if (NMNMreg == 0x4024)
350 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x403c, NMNM);
351
352 nvkm_wr32(device, Preg, Pval);
353 if (mpll) {
354 Pval &= ~(8 << 20);
355 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4020, Pval);
356 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4038, Pval);
357 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4600, saved4600);
358 }
359
360 nvkm_wr32(device, 0xc040, savedc040);
361
362 if (mpll) {
363 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4020, Pval & ~(1 << 28));
364 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4038, Pval & ~(1 << 28));
365 }
366}

368int
369nv04_devinit_pll_set(struct nvkm_devinit *devinit, u32 type, u32 freq)
370{
371 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &devinit->subdev;
372 struct nvkm_bios *bios = subdev->device->bios;
373 struct nvkm_pll_vals pv;
374 struct nvbios_pll info;
375 int cv = bios->version.chip;
376 int N1, M1, N2, M2, P;
377 int ret;
378
379 ret = nvbios_pll_parse(bios, type > 0x405c ? type : type - 4, &info);
380 if (ret)
381 return ret;
382
383 ret = nv04_pll_calc(subdev, &info, freq, &N1, &M1, &N2, &M2, &P);
384 if (!ret)
385 return -EINVAL;
386
387 pv.refclk = info.refclk;
388 pv.N1 = N1;
389 pv.M1 = M1;
390 pv.N2 = N2;
391 pv.M2 = M2;
392 pv.log2P = P;
393
394 if (cv == 0x30 || cv == 0x31 || cv == 0x35 || cv == 0x36 ||
395 cv >= 0x40) {
396 if (type > 0x405c)
397 setPLL_double_highregs(devinit, type, &pv);
398 else
399 setPLL_double_lowregs(devinit, type, &pv);
400 } else
401 setPLL_single(devinit, type, &pv);
402
403 return 0;
404}
405
406int
407nv04_devinit_post(struct nvkm_devinit *init, bool execute)
408{
409 return nvbios_init(&init->subdev, execute);
410}
411
412void
413nv04_devinit_preinit(struct nvkm_devinit *base)
414{
415 struct nv04_devinit *init = nv04_devinit(base);
416 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &init->base.subdev;
417 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
418
419 /* make i2c busses accessible */
420 nvkm_mask(device, 0x000200, 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
421
422 /* unslave crtcs */
423 if (init->owner < 0)
424 init->owner = nvkm_rdvgaowner(device);
425 nvkm_wrvgaowner(device, 0);
426
427 if (!init->base.post) {
428 u32 htotal = nvkm_rdvgac(device, 0, 0x06);
429 htotal |= (nvkm_rdvgac(device, 0, 0x07) & 0x01) << 8;
430 htotal |= (nvkm_rdvgac(device, 0, 0x07) & 0x20) << 4;
431 htotal |= (nvkm_rdvgac(device, 0, 0x25) & 0x01) << 10;
432 htotal |= (nvkm_rdvgac(device, 0, 0x41) & 0x01) << 11;
433 if (!htotal) {
434 nvkm_debug(subdev, "adaptor not initialised\n");
435 init->base.post = true;
436 }
437 }
438}
439
440void *
441nv04_devinit_dtor(struct nvkm_devinit *base)
442{
443 struct nv04_devinit *init = nv04_devinit(base);
444 /* restore vga owner saved at first init */
445 nvkm_wrvgaowner(init->base.subdev.device, init->owner);
446 return init;
447}
448
449int
450nv04_devinit_new_(const struct nvkm_devinit_func *func,
451 struct nvkm_device *device, int index,
452 struct nvkm_devinit **pinit)
453{
454 struct nv04_devinit *init;
455
456 if (!(init = kzalloc(sizeof(*init), GFP_KERNEL)))
457 return -ENOMEM;
458 *pinit = &init->base;
459
460 nvkm_devinit_ctor(func, device, index, &init->base);
461 init->owner = -1;
462 return 0;
463}
464
465static const struct nvkm_devinit_func
466nv04_devinit = {
467 .dtor = nv04_devinit_dtor,
468 .preinit = nv04_devinit_preinit,
469 .post = nv04_devinit_post,
470 .meminit = nv04_devinit_meminit,
471 .pll_set = nv04_devinit_pll_set,
472};
473
474int
475nv04_devinit_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index,
476 struct nvkm_devinit **pinit)
477{
478 return nv04_devinit_new_(&nv04_devinit, device, index, pinit);
479}
